## finalstrike.yaml

```yaml
version: '1'
project:
  name: sample-app
llm:
  provider: openai_compat
  base_url: http://localhost:11434/v1
  model: llama3
build:
  commands:
  - name: install
    run: pip install -r requirements.txt
    optional: false
tests:
  commands:
  - name: unit
    run: pytest -q
    optional: false
api:
  base_url: http://localhost:8080
  health:
  - method: GET
    path: /health
    expect_status: 200
ui:
  base_url: http://localhost:3000
  browser: chromium
  smoke_route: /
secrets:
  file: .finalstrike/secrets.env
evidence:
  video: true
  screenshots: true
  output_dir: .finalstrike/runs
slack: null
policy:
  fail_fast: false
  max_test_retries: 0
  max_ui_steps: 40
  max_ui_retries: 4
```

## Repository context
## AGENTS.md (/workspace/fixtures/sample-app/AGENTS.md)

# Sample App — FinalStrike fixture

Minimal API + static frontend used for FinalStrike integration testing.

## Services

| Service  | Port | Notes                    |
|----------|------|--------------------------|
| API      | 8080 | `GET /health` returns 200 |
| Frontend | 3000 | Static HTML smoke page   |

## Smoke routes

- UI: `http://localhost:3000/` — landing page with title "Sample App"
- API: `http://localhost:8080/health`

## Test commands

- `pytest -q` — unit tests in `tests/`

## Known gaps

- No authentication (intentional for fixture simplicity)
- No live third-party API integrations
- Task-list feature from `acceptance-full.md` is **planned** — see `capabilities.yaml`

## Environment
version: 1
install: pip install -r requirements.txt
terminals:
  - api: python3 -m sample_app.server
  - frontend: python3 -m http.server 3000 --directory static

## Acceptance Criteria

## Feature: Sample App smoke verification

### Acceptance Criteria

- API health endpoint returns 200 on GET /health
- Frontend landing page loads at / with title "Sample App"
- Unit tests pass via `pytest -q`

